<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-484-212  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 484 212.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  July 31 1989 n259 p10(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Users contest regionals' opposition to divestiture restrictions.andO;(brief filed by the Ad Hoc Telecommunications Users Committee)(regional Bell holding companies)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Killette, Kathleen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Ad Hoc Telecommunications Users Committee files briefs in theUS Court of Appeals supporting US District Judge Harold H.andO;Greene's 1987 and 1988 rulings in the ATandamp;T divestiture case.andO;Greene did ease the ban on the provision of non-content-basedinformation services by regional Bell holding companies.andP;  At thesame time, he maintained restrictions on manufacturing and theprovision of long distance services.andP;  The Ad Hoc Committee warnsthat relaxation of line-of-business restrictions would diminish ornegate the benefits of increased competition in the equipment,long-distance and information-services markets.andP;  Other groups,including ADAPSO, Dun andamp; Bradstreet and the Computer and BusinessEquipment Manufacturers Assn concurred.andP;  The briefs were opposedby the regional Bells and the US Dept of Justice.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Ad Hoc Telecommunications Users CommitteeBell Regional Holding CompaniesCommunications Service SuppliersLegal IssuesInformation ServicesUnited States. Department of JusticeDivestmentUser Groups.andO;Person:    Greene, Harold (cases).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>